in this time we will create a VM with the VHD file

First of all, make sure that you have installed all of depedencies of hyper-v, and your MotherBoard have the virtualization featur

typing 'windows+r' and then 'Virtmgmt.msc' to open hyper-v manager
in action menu by the right side you must see the 'new' option
new>Vitual machine> 
in specify generation you must choose 'generation 1' to MBR partition and lagacy boot 
or 'generation 2' to GPT partition and UEFI boot( in this point, in case of UEFI boot you must to convert the .vhd file in .vhdx.
and i will assume that you primary .tib file is a image of an MBR partition boot case, so if not i will make a another documentation for
how to convert the .vhd file)
specify generation>assign memory in there you must choose how much memory you want assign, i recomend 2048mb for win10
network>i think you dont will need, but if you need it google it! hahaha
conect virtual harddisk> using a exist virtual drive: find him! and next
next and finish!

time to start your VM > in most cases win10 will adapt by himself and initiate, in some we will make some adjust. 

